  "prompt": "How do I stop my dog from peeing on my bed?",
  "response": "Here are several strategies to stop your dog from peeing on your bed:\n\n1. Medical check\n- Rule out medical issues like urinary tract infections or bladder problems\n- Consult your veterinarian\n\n2. Address potential causes\n- Anxiety or stress\n- Lack of house training\n- Marking territory\n- Submission or excitement urination\n\n3. Training techniques\n- Increase potty training\n- Take frequent bathroom breaks\n- Reward good behavior\n- Use positive reinforcement\n- Establish a consistent routine\n\n4. Preventative measures\n- Close bedroom door\n- Use a crate when unsupervised\n- Use waterproof mattress covers\n- Clean any accidents thoroughly with enzymatic cleaner\n\n5. Behavioral strategies\n- Reduce anxiety\n- Create a safe, comfortable environment\n- Consider professional training\n- Use calming techniques if anxiety-related\n\n6. If persistent\n- Consult a professional dog trainer\n- Consider behavior modification techniques\n- Discuss potential medication with vet for anxiety\n\n7. Cleanup\n- Always clean accidents completely to remove scent\n- Use specialized pet urine removal products\n- Avoid punishing the dog, which can increase anxiety\n\nConsistency and patience are key in addressing this issue.",
